FBIS3-15181 "drsov042_a_94016" FBIS-SOV-94-042 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Mar 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Croatia's Granic Admits Downed Planes Took Off From Croatia LD0303083794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0729 GMT 3 Mar 94 LD0303083794 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Boris Sitnikov] [Text] United Nations Organisation March 3 TASS -- The planes, brought down in Bosnia, took off from the Croatian territory, Croatian Foreign Minister Mate Granic admitted on Wednesday [2 March] at the U.N. headquarters. Responding to the question of journalists, whether the planes, that were brought down, were Serb or Croatian, Granic said: "The planes flew from the zone, protected by the U.N., from the Nudvina airport. A permanent representative of Croatia at the U.N. has already informed of it the chairman of the Security Council. We suggested that the U.N. put that airport under control."
